</title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/6455/windows-key-is-mod-still-want-to-use-alt-for-some-combos/?comment=6457#comment-6457</link><description>This is essentially a duplicate of this question: https://faq.i3wm.org/question/6212/modshifta-works-strgalta-doesnt/</description><pubDate>Tue, 18 Aug 2015 21:59:13 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/6455/windows-key-is-mod-still-want-to-use-alt-for-some-combos/?comment=6457#comment-6457</guid></item><item><title>Answer by i3convert for &lt;p&gt;I have my windows key (Mod4) as $mod, but I want to use my Alt key for some key combinations (a few that don't conflict with emacs).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here's the snippet of my config that I wish would work, but isn't:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;#alternative switch to workspace:
bindsym Alt+1 workspace 1
bindsym Alt+2 workspace 2
bindsym Alt+3 workspace 3
bindsym Alt+4 workspace 4
bindsym Alt+5 workspace 5
bindsym Alt+6 workspace 6
bindsym Alt+7 workspace 7
bindsym Alt+8 workspace 8
bindsym Alt+9 workspace 9
bindsym Alt+0 workspace 10
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Am I doing something wrong?&lt;/p&gt;
 </title><link>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/6455/windows-key-is-mod-still-want-to-use-alt-for-some-combos/?answer=6456#post-id-6456</link><description>You should use `Mod1`, not `Alt`. Run `xmodmap` to see the list of bindings of keys to virtual modifier names.</description><pubDate>Tue, 18 Aug 2015 17:25:59 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://faq.i3wm.org/question/6455/windows-key-is-mod-still-want-to-use-alt-for-some-combos/?answer=6456#post-id-6456</guid></item></channel></rss>